{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":128201,"duration_api_ms":127777,"num_turns":25,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"3284fbf1-e0ca-4b84-8e90-edf470fc37ec","total_cost_usd":1.0948857500000002,"usage":{"input_tokens":13,"cache_creation_input_tokens":80001,"cache_read_input_tokens":950529,"output_tokens":4782,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":80001,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":13,"outputTokens":4782,"cacheReadInputTokens":950529,"cacheCreationInputTokens":80001,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":1.0948857500000002,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"evidence":["All 99 milestone_record tests pass (0 failures, 0 ignored) — verified by running cargo test --lib contexts::milestone_record","cargo clippy -- -D warnings passes cleanly (no warnings)","cargo fmt --all --check passes (no formatting issues)","Amendment fr-14-b5a477a3 VERIFIED: TaskRunEntry.milestone_id is now `pub milestone_id: String` (model.rs:276) — no Option wrapper, no #[serde(default)], no skip_serializing_if. read_task_runs_from_path (fs.rs:2478-2501) directly deserializes entries without any backfill logic. canonicalize_entry_for_write is fully removed (grep returns zero matches). The milestone_id field is required in the JSON schema.","Amendment fr-14-c5bceaec VERIFIED: CompletionJournalDetails::parse (fs.rs:2283-2285) now does JSON-only parsing via serde_json::from_str — no parse_legacy fallback. The repairable_completion_event function (fs.rs:2382-2405) only handles JSON-parseable completion events; the legacy 'starts_with(\"project=\")' branch is completely removed. Grep for 'parse_legacy' returns zero matches.","Amendment fr-14-1ac821d9 VERIFIED: The backward-compat test task_run_entry_backward_compat_without_new_fields has been removed (grep returns zero matches). The legacy-backfill test read_task_runs_backfills_milestone_id_for_legacy_entries has been removed (grep returns zero matches). The progress_deserialization_defaults_skipped_beads test has been removed (grep returns zero matches), and skipped_beads is now a required field — no #[serde(default)] annotation on it (model.rs:204).","Amendment fr-14-89e13c37 (planner rejected, voter rejected): CORRECTLY NOT APPLIED — _started_at parameter was actually renamed to started_at and IS NOW USED in find_matching_running_task_run (model.rs:416). The function uses started_at to match same-attempt replays (lines 434 and 441: entry.started_at == started_at).","Amendment fr-14-c6ca5e53 (planner rejected, voter rejected): CORRECTLY SCOPED — milestone_id was made required (per b5a477a3), legacy journal parsing was removed (per c5bceaec), but run_id, plan_hash, and outcome_detail correctly remain Optional with serde(default, skip_serializing_if) because they are legitimately unknown at some write paths.","Amendment fr-14-ec2442bd VERIFIED: find_matching_running_task_run (model.rs:411-447) now uses started_at as a discriminator. For run_id=Some: first matches exact run_id, then falls back to sole runless entry only if entry.started_at == started_at (line 434). For run_id=None: matches sole runless entry only if entry.started_at == started_at (line 441). Different started_at means a new retry, not a replay — the function returns None, causing a new row to be appended.","Test regressions added: runless_retry_with_new_started_at_appends_new_attempt and named_replay_with_matching_started_at_backfills_runless_attempt verify the new started_at-based discrimination between retries and replays.","model.rs: All centralized helpers remain correct — same_attempt (300), merge_attempt_entries, collapse_task_run_attempts, latest_task_runs_per_bead, active_bead_ids, find_matching_running_task_run (411), has_finalized_task_run (449)","service.rs: All mutation paths (update_status, persist_plan, record_bead_start, update_task_run) run under with_milestone_write_lock for serialized access","service.rs: reconcile_snapshot_from_lineage rebuilds counters from latest_task_runs_per_bead, preserves Paused, transitions Active→Ready when no active beads remain"],"findings_or_gaps":["All six final-review amendments have been correctly addressed: fr-14-b5a477a3 (milestone_id required), fr-14-c5bceaec (legacy parsing removed), fr-14-1ac821d9 (backward-compat tests removed) were accepted and implemented; fr-14-89e13c37 (remove _started_at) was rejected and the parameter is now actively used; fr-14-c6ca5e53 (broad optional removal) was rejected and correctly scoped to only milestone_id; fr-14-ec2442bd (started_at discrimination) was accepted and implemented.","AppError::RunStartFailed is still used for rejecting non-terminal outcomes in update_task_run (semantically a finalization rejection). A more specific error variant would be cleaner but this is cosmetic, not a correctness issue — carried forward from prior reviews.","The outstanding risk — milestone mutations span separate lineage, snapshot, and journal files without a cross-file transaction — remains. All paths are serialized by the milestone mutation lock and replay-safe, making this an acceptable trade-off for file-based storage.","The get_or_insert_with on run_id at fs.rs:3014 is in the update_task_run finalization path (backfilling run_id on a non-terminal entry being completed), which is legitimate — not related to the removed milestone_id backfill."],"follow_up_or_amendments":[],"outcome":"approved"},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"f4cb7dbe-b579-42c6-a4ee-b1faa7b41a14"}
